[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_07qi4")
release_version = "v1.2.0"
notes = "[TITLE]Highlights
Added 2 new characters: Professor Pete and Lil Oldman
  The achievements menu has hints for their unlock conditions
Added a new alternate floor: The Molten Mint
A Stranger has appeared... somewhere...
  They can be found... somehow...
  Will you accept their offer?
Added 19 new accessory items
Added 8 new pocket prank items
Added 5 new passive items
Added 3 new anomalies
Added 7 new Proxy Cog abilities
Added 4 new Proxy Cogs, 3 of which were from the Summer 2025 Community-Crafted Cogs Contest. Specific credits can be found in the Proxy Cogs section below!
Added 11 new achievements
Revamped the Pick-A-Toon screen
  When choosing a character, you can now use a custom seed for your run. Great for competing with friends or to share a crazy run you had with others
[TITLE]Engine
Updated to Godot version 4.5
Back-end rewrite to run randomization to better support seeded runs
[TITLE]Items
Added Accessories:
  Toonosaur Hat (1-Star)
  Masquerade Mask (2-Star)
  Plush Bear Pack (2-Star)
  Bee Hive Hairdo (2-Star)
  Toonosaur Boots (3-Star)
  Danger Shades (3-Star)
  Airplane Wings (3-Star)
  Fishing Hat (3-Star)
  Small Pouch (3-Star)
  Dragonfly Wings (3-Star)
  Smooch Glasses (3-Star)
  Bird Wings (3-Star) (Locked)
  Butterfly Wings (4-Star)
  Motorcycle Boots (4-Star)
  Napoleon Hat (4-Star)
  Weird Glasses (4-Star) (Locked)
  Large Pouch (5-Star)
  Spider Legs (5-Star)
  Super Toon Boots (5-Star)
Added Pocket Pranks:
  Spinning Top (1-Star)
  Calculator (2-Star)
  Moneybags Coin (2-Star)
  Book of Laws (3-Star) (Locked)
  Glowering Dagger (3-Star) (Locked)
  Spinach Can (3-Star)
  Watering Can (3-Star)
  Recycle Bin (4-Star)
Added Passive Items:
  Rolodex (2-Star) (Locked)
  Red Tape (3-Star)
  Wacky Whistle (3-Star)
  Philosopher's Stone (4-Star) (Locked)
  Dilly Dial (5-Star) (Locked)
Balance Tweaks:
  Cowboy Hat now has a damage penalty of -15%
  Made Cowboy Hat slightly rarer
  Paint Bucket now rerolls all the items in the room
  Sandwich can now be used in battle
  Cash Register now grants a 10% Damage boost for 1 round for 3 beans each
  Gag Button is now a 4-Star item rather than a 3-Star item
  Gumball Machine's base super candy chance has been reduced to 15%
    This chance will now scale to 30% at 200% Luck
  Goggles is now displayed as a 4-Star item rather than a 5-Star item (rarity is unchanged)
  Balancing Scale is now a 3-Star item rather than a 5-Star item
  Pompadour Hairdo now gives +4% to all stats and -8% damage instead of +2% to all stats and -10% damage
  Fedora now gives +5% Luck
  Wizard Hat and Crown now give +3% Luck
  Hats that boost damage for specific departments (Bowler Hat, Police Hat, etc.) now boost 15% instead of 10%, and also affect defense against that department
  Jester Hat is now a 4-Star item and doubles Toon-Up effects instead of adding a flat +20%
  Pirate Hat now gives 2-4 jellybeans per Proxy defeated instead of just 2
  Archer Hat luck boost per Gag has been increased from 2.5% to 4%
  Mask now gives +20% Evasiveness instead of +10%
  Super Toon Cape now gives +10% Evasiveness instead of +5%
  Eye Patch now gives -10% Luck instead of -15%
  Heart Glasses and Mini Blinds now scale with luck
  Bee Wings now convert 50% of Speed into Crit damage instead of 75%
  Laff Boosts now scale based on the treasure chest they are found in
  Laff Boosts no longer spawn naturally from item pools
    (This just means Laff Boosts are more directly managed by the game logic, you will still see plenty)
  The Zippy Zap candy now boosts speed by 5% rather than 3%
  Treasures now give a 33% heal instead of a 25% heal on pick-up, with a minimum of +1 Laff
  Treasures now become rarer the more you have
  You can now only carry 7 treasures across all types
  Made Gag Track Frames relatively inexpensive when in the shop
  Made Stat Candies a little less expensive when in the shop
  Evasiveness Stat Candies now give +5% for their regular variant and +12% for their super variant
  Feather now adds +30% Defense rather than +20%
  Bamboo Cane now adds +40% Evasiveness rather than +20%
  Juggling Cubes now adds +20% Luck rather than +10%
  Defense, Evasiveness, and Luck have also had their High Dive effects increased
Misc:
  Updated the description for Pixie Dust to be more in line with other consumables
  Added a quick grow-in sequence for world items
  Majorly reorganized the item pools across the entire game
    Specifically, no Accessory/Pocket Prank can appear in more than two item pools (minus a few outliers)
  For example, the Wooden Sword used to be available as a Floor Clear reward, in Shops, as well as Gold and Special Treasure Chests, and is now only available in two locations
[TITLE]Toons
Implemented full ToonDNA, meaning...
  All Toon body combinations from Toontown Online are now possible
  All previously missing Toon animations are now available to us
  Mixed body actions are now theoretically possible (though not implemented) like throwing a pie while running
  Toons are now capable of wearing shoes
Added some new clothing types
Implementing these new bodies was a very big under-the-hood change we may have missed a few small visual issues with, so please let us know about any bugs you find
[TITLE]Gags
The damage reductions of group Lure Gags now increase over the track
Group Lure Gags now also apply an accuracy down on Cogs
The damage of Banana Peel, Rake and Marbles have all been increased
[TITLE]Characters
Added Professor Pete
Added Lil Oldman
Clara will now keep 10% of the boosts she obtains on the floor permanently
When at full Laff, Clara can no longer roll an HP boost from Trap
Clara can now hear in the dark (we fixed her ear size)
Bessie's Drop will now activate as the final move of her turn, rather than the first
Slightly increased Moe Zart's self heal and damage boosts
All Character DNA has been updated to properly reflect their Toontown Online DNA
[TITLE]Bosses
A new Boss has appeared, ready for a heated confrontation
Damage in the Head of Security boss fight will now increase with each mistake made
Slightly nerfed HP values of the Directors to 2500
Increased the damage dealt by the Directors
Made a sizeable increase to the damage of Traffic Manager's Traffic Jam & Bookkeeper's Reprimand
Union Buster's Liability Waver & Contract Limit moves now queue at the end of the round
Cogs are no longer queued to spawn every round when Union Buster is in the fight
Added new music to the Paint Silo boss
Added new music to the Barrel Room (the room before the Directors boss fight)
Allowing the static meter to reach the top in the Slendercog boss battle will now result in an instant defeat
Made a few changes to some boss cutscenes where Toons would annoyingly clip into the camera
Changed the name of the Security Goon's attack to \"Ex post facto Law\"
Buttons that are almost immediately stomped in the Golden Goose fight will prompt another button to spawn quickly after
Implemented anti Cog farming measures to bosses like Chartist and Ground Floor Investor where reinforcements can spawn infinitely 
Some bosses now have a typewriter effect to introduce their names in their cutscenes
[TITLE]Title Screen
Overhauled the Pick-A-Toon menu to be more versatile, including a full UI refresh
Added a custom run seed field
  Any custom seed will be displayed under the game timer to differentiate custom seed runs from random seed runs
[TITLE]Facilities
Added the Molten Mint
Certain obstacle rooms will now add charges to your Pocket Prank on completion
Added Pistons so it is now possible to backtrack from the Ground Floor Investor fight without the \"I'm stuck!\" button
Added three new anomalies
Added some new rooms to all standard facility floors
Mazes in the Cog Golf Course will now only have a 2 cog battle instead of a 4 cog battle at the end
The D.A. Office has a new shop
The Mint has new battle music
The \"Big Puzzle\" special room in the D.A. Office will now only deal damage when you fail Skull Finder
  The big puzzle can no longer be the \"Run!\" puzzle
Slightly increased the difficulty of the Pathfinder special room puzzle
The Haunted Cog Golf Course is now 33% brighter
Facility Alt Floors are now slightly more common
Updated the appearance of some rooms
Moving obstacles will now have the same position between game releases
The \"Inspiration\" anomaly will now tell you which stat is boosted in its description
Tightened Security and Faulty Security, when combined, will now synergize into lowering the Cog level range minimum by 1, and increasing the Cog level range maximum by 1, stopping both of them from cancelling each other out
Increased the bean reward range of Record Profits
Double Trouble's v2.0 Cog rolls are now properly seeded
The length of floors will now vary slightly
Added a few more anomalies to the mid-floor blocklist
Facility obstacles now use your defense stat in damage calculations
Slightly decreased the hitbox size of the rolling golf ball
Fences in the Cog Golf Course will no longer take control of your camera for their opening cutscene
Slightly updated a few room obstacles to be more challenging
[TITLE]Cogs
Cogs have been made slightly stronger overall
Added Restraining Order
[TITLE]Proxy Cogs
Three brand new community-crafted Proxy Cogs have been spotted in Cog HQ!
  Stickler by Jackyland
  Live Wire by Evelyn (Velvet Petunia)
  Cash Cow by JustaBluToon & DoggoMafia
An additional Proxy Cog has appeared in Cog HQ
Added seven new Proxy Cog abilities
Viper has received a makeover
[TITLE]Cog Creator
Clicking \"New\" will now swap to a random, standard Cog DNA
Added a field to give a custom nametag suffix to a Cog
The Proxy toggle will no longer appear until you have completed your first run
[TITLE]Tweaks
Items can now be locked behind achievements
You can now enable/disable installed mods in the Settings panel
You can now use F3 to toggle some GUI assets
Classic Control's turn speed is now based on the player's speed stat
Classic Control players can now use the orbital camera via right-click
Added support for mouse controls, you can use left-click to move forward, and right-click to jump
  Note: Mouse controls are only supported in the \"Default\" control style
Added a keybind for re-centering the camera
Individual \"turns\" are now referred to as \"moves\" for clarity, to elaborate...
  Move: A singular battle action
  Turn: The set of moves a battle participant makes during the round
  Round: The combined set of all battle participants' turns before move selection restarts
Added a keybind for taking screenshots
Jump height is no longer lowered by platforms moving downwards
Stat boost status effects are now additive instead of multiplicative
You can now earn the respect of the credits panel
Achievements now support hints
The achievement panel now supports sections
Added a pity system for a rare achievement
Changed the name of the 100% completion achievement
Decreased the hitbox size of the burner obstacle
Added support for sub-bullet points in the release notes panel
  They look like this!
Fixed a few places where treasure chests were a little too embedded into the ground
Refactored a ton of the game's inner workings
The Game Timer will now turn yellow when paused
Win Streaks can now be negative
Added a developer console
NPC Toons now wear random accessories
ToonTasks are now rolled at the start of the Ground Floor
Improved the look of a few battle movies
Invincibility frames are now denoted by your Toon flashing blue for a short time
Implemented a method of forcing the game to cache heavy shaders on startup
  This loading screen should be much quicker on subsequent startups than on first startup
  Modified the appearance of the loading screen to match the shader compiler menu
[TITLE]Bugfixes
Fixed a bug where Toons would spin violently when jumping on a golf cart
Fixed a bug where moles could occasionally launch the player downwards
Fixed the rotation of the Squirting Flower on tall Toons
Fixed a bug where Doodle names would change upon adoption
Definitely and for real this time fixed Toon decapitation on the game over screen
Cogs now properly walk backwards when unlured
Walking backwards in the Classic Control style will also now properly play the animation backwards
Implemented a fix for the going sad animation not playing properly on some occasions
Fixed a bug where the text on the statistics menu could run over the bounds of the panel by introducing a character limit
Added protection against total playtime corruption
Fixed a bug with a skirt that was accidentally untextured
Fixed some pop-in when the boss of The Factory is loaded in
The Game Timer will now properly re-sync on loading a save file
Swapping out Pocket Pranks at shops is less finicky
Drop shadows are now functional with animations in battle
Fixed a rendering issue with horse Toon pupils
Fixed an issue where you would not get invincibility frames after being revived
Fixed an issue where using Trap on an already Lured Cog with Detective Hat would not correctly apply knockback damage if the player also had Safari Hat
Fixed a bug where Witch Hat's poison damage wouldn't be scaled by your stats
Fixed an issue where damage could apply twice in the Head of Security Boss Fight
Fixed an issue where Cogs would not be counted towards ToonTasks when fired
Fixed the Diverse Portfolio Proxy effect not applying its damage reduction properly
Fixed a bug where the title screen music would restart on leaving the Cog Creator
Fixed an exploit in the D.A. Office
Fixed a bug where you could gain prank charges from Virtual Skelecog battles
Fixed an issue where Cowboy Hat would still give the Deadeye bonus in Virtual Skelecog battles
Fixed an issue in the Head of Security boss that allowed you to stand on the skulls in the \"Get to the Safe Zone\" round
Fixed some miscellaneous damage source reporting issues
Fixed a long-standing animation issue with the fat Cog body type where its left shoulder was misaligned
Fixed a bug where Ground Floor ToonTasks would ask for Cogs that could not appear on the Ground Floor due to their level minimum
  Relatedly, this also fixes the issue where tier 1 Cogs (Flunky, Cold Caller, etc.) could not appear in ToonTasks at all
Minor text fixes
[TITLE]For Modders
The setup for item pools has changed significantly
  Item pools no longer contain arrays of item resources, but file paths to item resources
  Implementing modded items must now be done via the new item pool function \"add_items\"
Proxy Cog effects are now stored in a static variable rather than a constant
MaxToonupConsumables in Globals is now a variable rather than a constant
With the introduction of full ToonDNA, any modded character's DNA should be re-assessed as they will be given small legs by default
Implementing different battle speeds is no longer a hassle if you use SettingsFile.add_battle_speed()
Gag accuracy can now be reimplemented by setting \"use_accuracy\" to true on the Player object
Dynamic Battle Nodes no longer have a soft cap of 4 Cogs
Whether or not a Cog counts towards ToonTasks and certain item benefits (like Cowboy Hat) has been refactored to not rely on the Virtual Skelecog toggle
Added a signal for the settings menu opening (Globals.s_settings_opened)
RandomService has been deprecated and is now replaced by the RNG class
  RandomService will still work as expected for now, but may be fully removed in the future
  As part of this refactor, the 'true_random' channel is no longer needed, and Godot's built-in random functions should be used instead
  Here is an example of using the new RNG class:
  Before: RandomService.randi_channel('floors')
  After: RNG.channel(RNG.ChannelFloors).randi()
For Pocket Pranks: the cancel_use function is now deprecated and will be removed in a future version
  To write custom logic to cancel the use of a Pocket Prank, override the new function validate_use
Pocket Pranks now have a toggle option to allow use when not at full charge
HP Overheal can now be enabled on BattleStats via \"allow_overheal\"
Custom achievements can now be added to the achievement panel via SaveFileService.add_achievement
  In order to get the most mileage out of it, you'll need your own system of tracking your custom achievements, and a custom script extending from the Achievement resource type that overrides the need to check the vanilla progress file for if an achievement is unlocked
The upgrade to Godot 4.5 has changed how duplicate() works, and although the migration guide claims it should still maintain original functionality, there's likely to be some changes you need to make if you used it regularly in your mods (like using duplicate(true) to get a resource with all of its properties duplicated properly)"
